entry.title: Special Weather Statement issued September 15 at 6:07PM AKDT by NWS
entry.summary: ...TRACE ASHFALL POSSIBLE FOR UNIMAK ISLAND... As of 0540 PM this evening, satellite imagery indicates that an eruption is ongoing at Shishaldin Volcano. Ash is being lofted to the north and east of the volcano, which may lead to trace amounts of ashfall for the communities of False Pass, King Cove, and Cold Bay. This statement will be updated if conditions change.
